;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":812,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/26\/overly-judgmental-muslims\/","url_meta":{"origin":32348,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Condemning: Overly judgmental Muslims are most astray","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 26, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cIf a man says the people are ruined, he is the most ruined among them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2623 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Nawawi said, \"The scholars agree that this disapproval refers only to those\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/07\/never-say-allah-not-forgive\/","url_meta":{"origin":32348,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Arrogance: Never say Allah will not forgive someone","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Jundab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cA man said: By Allah, Allah will not forgive this person! Allah Almighty said: Who is he who swore by Me that I will not forgive someone? I have forgiven him and erased your good deeds.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32376,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/19\/earth-swallows-man-pride\/","url_meta":{"origin":32348,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Vanity: Earth swallows man dragging his garment","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 19, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhile a man was trailing his robe out of vanity, he was suddenly swallowed up, and he will be buried in the earth until the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5790 Grade: Sahih (authentic)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25966,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/02\/22\/unnecessary-questions-arrogance\/","url_meta":{"origin":32348,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Questions: Asking unnecessary questions arrogantly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 22, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019d reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAmong the most criminal of Muslims towards other Muslims are those who ask about a matter that is not forbidden, then it becomes forbidden for people due to his questioning.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6859, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2358\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24793,"url":"ht